import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('lookup_people.csv')

# Plot age distribution
sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
plt.title('What is the age distribution of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="job_title", data=data, palette="Set2")
    ax.set(xlabel='Job Title', ylabel='Count')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_people.csv')
chart = plot(data)
plt.title('What is the distribution of job titles in the dataset?', wrap=True)
plt.show()
```
